snippet.textDisplay: shooting at 3000 frames / second the 1.5 (or 2 inch dart) takes 6 frames from entering frame to fully on screen (as well as 6 frames from impact to fully seated) thus. 6 frames / 3000 frames/second = 0.002 seconds, 1.5 inches / 0.002 seconds = 750 inches / second = 62.5 feet per second (or 83.3 feet per second if it is a 2 inch needle).
